STYLE TECHNIQUES

<h1 style="color:blue;">Hello World </h1>
<h1><span style="color:blue">Hello World</span> </h1>

<h1 style="font-family:impact;">This is a heading</h1>

<h1 style="font-size:300%;">This is a heading</h1>
<p style="font-size:160%;">This is a paragraph.</p>


<h1 style="text-align:center;">Centered heading</h1>
<p style="text-align:center;">This is a paragraph.</p>


FORMATTING

<strong>dk</strong>
<b>This text is bold.</b>

<h2>HTML <small>Small</small> Formatting</h2>               small font size decreasd
<h2>HTML <mark>Marked</mark> Formatting</h2>                Marked will b given a backgroung color

<p>My favorite color is <del>blue</del> red.</p>            blue is crossed
<ins>color</ins>                                            color is underlined

<p>This is <sub>subscripted</sub> text.</p>
<p>This is <sup>superscripted</sup> text.</p>               suffix type


Quotations

<p>WWF's goal is to: <q>Build a future where people live in harmony with nature.</q></p>         The HTML <q> element defines a short quotation.

<p>The <abbr title="World Health Organization">WHO</abbr> was founded in 1948.</p>           Marking abbreviations can give useful information  .                                                                                            to browsers, translation systems and search-engines
